The evidence with the title 'Why we still need the Voting Rights Act - The Washington Post ' says Feb 24, 2013  ... The Voting Rights Act still serves a purpose .  ... Vote of 390 to 33 in the House and 98 to 0 in the Senate . Opponents of Section 5 complain of state expense, yet their only cost is the paper , postage and manpower required to send copies of legislation to the federal government for review , hardly a punishment. 
